  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (COMPOUND-03 adversarial sample)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification was performed across all five flow-speed combinations; seven of thirteen credibility factors were formally assessed and six were scoped out as epistemic gaps. The assessment team concluded that the body of evidence, taken together with the UQ campaign, supported a Medium assurance level and an Accepted decision. NOTE (adversarial): one factor carries achievedLevel below requiredLevel with an Accepted outcome, triggering W-AR-02 and rendering the Medium assurance declaration unsupportable (COMPOUND-03).",
  "couName": "VAD use",
  "decision": "Accepted",
  "deviceClass": "Class III",
  "modelRiskLevel": 5,
  "bindsRequirement": "https://uofa.net/synth/req/vad-hemolysis-mrl5",
  "bindsClaim": "https://uofa.net/synth/claim/vad-hemolysis-absolute-threshold",
