      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "In-vitro hemolysis bench comparison — normalised index",
      "description": "Normalised index of hemolysis (NIH) measured across 3 operating points and compared to CFD-derived hemolysis power-law predictions. Agreement within 18% at two points; one outlier at high-speed low-flow condition showing 31% over-prediction. Monte Carlo sensitivity analysis attributes discrepancy to uncertainty in red-cell fragility coefficient."
    }
  ],
